The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, July 29, 2004 				 Numaligarh shutdown
																								July 28: Numaligarh Refinery Ltd (NRL) has been shut down as the railways have not been able to evacuate its products due to the damage caused to the tracks by the flood.																								According to senior Bharat Petroleum officials, the refinery is expected to remain closed for another week or so. BPCL markets the products in the northern and eastern parts of the country. It will now be picking up these products from Indian Oil Corporation. 
